-- Corrected: Emerson profit rises 14 percent
-- 
-- Tue May 1, 2007 7:09am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/01/us-emerson-results-corrected-idUSWEN735320070501

 

 (Corrects year-earlier profit figure to $434 million) 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Emerson Electric Co. ( EMR.N ) reported higher quarterly profit on Tuesday, driven by international demand across its portfolio. Earnings rose 14 percent to $494 million, or 61 cents per share, from $434 million, or 52 cents per share, a year earlier. Analysts on average expected profit of 60 cents per share, according to Reuters Estimates. Revenue rose 15 percent to $5.5 billion, compared with Wall Street forecasts of $5.4 billion. St. Louis-based Emerson, whose portfolio includes motors, thermostats, storage units for supermarkets, and technology to improve manufacturing efficiency, stood by its full-year earnings forecast of $2.50 to $2.60 per share. Analysts expect $2.59.